==English==
===Etymology===
[[umpteen]] + [[-th]]

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːnθ|-iːnθ]]

===Adjective===
'''umpteenth'''

#(''informal, often slightly derogatory'') Occurring in a relatively large but unspecified position in a series.
#:''That's the umpteenth time I've had to tell him not to swear in front of the children.''

====Translations====
*Swedish: [[femtioelfte]]
*Italian: [[ennesimo]]

====Synonyms====
*[[nth|''n''th]]
*umpty-umpth

===Noun===
'''umpteenth'''

#(''informal, often slightly derogatory'') The person or thing in the umpteenth position in a series.

===Related terms===
*[[umpteen]]

